The trade and industry portfolio committee will tomorrow discuss President Cyril Ramaphosa's reservations over parts of the Copyright Amendment Bill and Performers’ Protection Amendment Bill. Among the issues flagged sections are the right to freedom of trade, occupation and profession, and a lack of public comment on the fair use of artistic work. SA Guild of Actors Chairperson, Jack Devnarain joins us to discuss this. Courtesy #DSv403 JOHANNESBURG - The trade and industry portfolio committee is set to discuss President Cyril Ramaphosa's reservations over parts of the Copyright Amendment Bill and Performers’ Protection Amendment Bill. READ: Making sense of SA's new copyright bill and US trade threats Among the issues flagged are the right to freedom of trade, occupation and profession and a lack of public comment on the fair use of artistic work. SA Guild of Actors Chairperson Jack Devnarain said while this is another delay, it is an important step in ensuring actors get more value for their work.